at 7:51 pm </time> </a></div></footer><div class="comment-content"><p>But wait. I use Duolingo. It&#8217;s free<br /> As long as you put up with a couple advertisements.</p></div></article></li><li id="comment-45897" class="comment even depth-2"><article id="div-comment-45897" class="comment-body"><footer class="comment-meta"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/933df8a5725a6985827d33801f665df6?s=130&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/933df8a5725a6985827d33801f665df6?s=260&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-130 photo' height='130' width='130' /> <b class="fn">Kim Tae</b> <span class="says">says:</span></div><div class="comment-metadata"> <a href="https://10mag.com/10-of-the-best-free-korean-learning-apps/#comment-45897" data-wpel-link="internal"> <time datetime="2018-10-17T09:50:23+09:00"> October 17, 2018 at 9:50 am </time> </a></div></footer><div class="comment-content"><p>It’s bed better to use “Korean language; Drop.”</p></div></article></li><li id="comment-45979" class="comment odd alt depth-2"><article id="div-comment-45979" class="comment-body"><footer class="comment-meta"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7ca2237498f0be1a6d9b6241d6e61c88?s=130&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/7ca2237498f0be1a6d9b6241d6e61c88?s=260&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-130 photo' height='130' width='130' /> <b class="fn">jenny</b> <span class="says">says:</span></div><div class="comment-metadata"> <a href="https://10mag.com/10-of-the-best-free-korean-learning-apps/#comment-45979" data-wpel-link="internal"> <time datetime="2019-01-05T00:03:42+09:00"> January 5, 2019 at 12:03 am </time> </a></div></footer><div class="comment-content"><p>Actually if you don&#8217;t have any good apps or you can&#8217;t pay then there is no other option&#8230;because usually Every app contains purchases&#8230;</p></div></article></li></ol></li><li id="comment-41702" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent"><article id="div-comment-41702" class="comment-body"><footer class="comment-meta"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/459ec95ff6eda63d623c4d2b64c7d759?s=130&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/459ec95ff6eda63d623c4d2b64c7d759?s=260&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-130 photo' height='130' width='130' /> <b class="fn">daniel</b> <span class="says">says:</span></div><div class="comment-metadata"> <a href="https://10mag.com/10-of-the-best-free-korean-learning-apps/#comment-41702" data-wpel-link="internal"> <time datetime="2014-08-05T18:15:41+09:00"> August 5, 2014 at 6:15 pm </time> </a></div></footer><div class="comment-content"><p>ankidroid is also a good one to learn Korean.  It&#8217;s a flashcard memory learning system where if you know the word or sentence it repeats after 1 or 2 or 3 or 10 days&#8230;  All the uni korean courses are here plus a whole lot more.</p></div><div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://10mag.com/10-of-the-best-free-korean-learning-apps/?replytocom=41702#respond" data-commentid="41702" data-postid="41753" data-belowelement="div-comment-41702" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label="Reply to daniel" data-wpel-link="internal">Reply</a></div></article><ol class="children"><li id="comment-41703" class="comment odd alt depth-2"><article id="div-comment-41703" class="comment-body"><footer class="comment-meta"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3afee01e0626380503e381da1172f0b0?s=130&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3afee01e0626380503e381da1172f0b0?s=260&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-130 photo' height='130' width='130' /> <b class="fn"><a href="https://10mag.com" rel="external nofollow ugc noopener" class="url" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank">Anjee</a></b> <span class="says">says:</span></div><div class="comment-metadata"> <a href="https://10mag.com/10-of-the-best-free-korean-learning-apps/#comment-41703" data-wpel-link="internal"> <time datetime="2014-08-05T18:23:18+09:00"> August 5, 2014 at 6:23 pm </time> </a></div></footer><div class="comment-content"><p>Thanks, Daniel!<br /> Great suggestion as well. :)</p></div></article></li></ol></li><li id="comment-41700" class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent"><article id="div-comment-41700" class="comment-body"><footer class="comment-meta"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3afee01e0626380503e381da1172f0b0?s=130&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/3afee01e0626380503e381da1172f0b0?s=260&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-130 photo' height='130' width='130' /> <b class="fn"><a href="https://10mag.com" rel="external nofollow ugc noopener" class="url" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank">Anjee</a></b> <span class="says">says:</span></div><div class="comment-metadata"> <a href="https://10mag.com/10-of-the-best-free-korean-learning-apps/#comment-41700" data-wpel-link="internal"> <time datetime="2014-08-05T17:26:26+09:00"> August 5, 2014 at 5:26 pm </time> </a></div></footer><div class="comment-content"><p>Thanks Jesse!  That seems like a pretty good one, too!</p></div><div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="https://10mag.com/10-of-the-best-free-korean-learning-apps/?replytocom=41700#respond" data-commentid="41700" data-postid="41753" data-belowelement="div-comment-41700" data-respondelement="respond" aria-label="Reply to Anjee" data-wpel-link="internal">Reply</a></div></article><ol class="children"><li id="comment-42048" class="comment odd alt depth-2"><article id="div-comment-42048" class="comment-body"><footer class="comment-meta"><div class="comment-author vcard"> <img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/a